We all know internet trolls exist‚Ä¶but this celebrity just got trolled by someone very close to him‚Ä¶his mom. We all know what its like to be embarrassed by our parents I know I definitely do‚Ä¶and if you don‚Äôt well consider yourself lucky. 

However‚Ä¶unfortunately for Brooklyn Beckham his mom is a celebrity‚Ä¶so when she posts about him on social media it goes out to everyone. A little different than us non celebrities. I feel for yah Brooklyn‚Ä¶I wish I could relate but‚Ä¶ my parents don‚Äôt have over 14 million followers on Instagram like your mom.

Victoria Beckahm posted this silly pic of Brooklyn sleeping on a train ride while they were traveling together on Instagram live. Apparently the mother son duo were on their way to France. This just goes to show no matter how old us kids get‚Ä¶our parents will still think were at our cutest state while asleep. Victoria captioned the Instagram story post which features Brooklyn fast asleep with arm in a sling, headphones in, and vintage camera in tow with‚Ä¶ ‚ÄúHe‚Äôs a laugh.‚Äù

Although the sling does have me slightly concerned‚Ä¶it is worth mentioning his dad David got in on fun-making too. Because hello, you can‚Äôt have a funny picture without dear old dad chiming in. David Beckahm commented on the Instagram live stream saying ‚ÄúU should be at school‚Äù and then ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs my shirt‚Äù

Does anyone else think this is hilarious and adorable all at the same time like me? I can‚Äôt get enough. Just a few hours later‚Ä¶Victoria continued to brag about her baby boy this time posting a more flattering photo of Brooklyn holding the same camera as seen before with the caption ‚ÄúX VB‚Äù

It‚Äôs no shocker to see pictures of Brooklyn with a camera constantly by his side considering he‚Äôs already shot a fragrance campaign for Burberry. Parents‚Ä¶.how would anyone know about our accomplishments if we didn‚Äôt have them to brag about them for us?! As always‚Ä¶I want to know what you think. Videos compile: Catalan Referendum: Civil guard move in on polling stations amid vote
Catalonia's disputed independence referendum rapidly descended into chaos on Sunday as Spanish national police raided polling stations and clashed with voters.

Barcelona's deputy mayor said police fired rubber bullets at people as they attempted to vote in the referendum, which Spain's top court has declared illegal.
Catalan President Carles Puigdemont condemned "indiscriminate aggression" against people attempting to vote peacefully. Regional authorities said 38 people were treated by emergency services by mid-morning...

Un motivo, por otro lado inmejorable, para publicar el primer recopilatorio de su carrera. Con ‚ÄúBasurillas‚Äù, su guitarra favorita, presidiendo la portada. Y con un mont√≥n de esas canciones que ya son parte de todos y cada uno de nosotros. Dos DVDs. Uno con la recopilaci√≥n de todos sus videoclips y el otro con una largu√≠sima entrevista con el protagonista. Y tres discos. Los dos primeros dedicados a una selecci√≥n que √©l mismo ha escogido entre su amplia trayectoria, y un tercero con las colaboraciones de los numerosos amigos que ha ido haciendo durante todo este tiempo. Porque es imposible conocerle y no quererle. Y eso se refleja tambi√©n en el impecable y rotundo libro que acompa√±a a este lanzamiento, con periodistas y compa√±eros de profesi√≥n hablando del tipo de la gorra calada. Ah√≠ est√°n Carlos Tarque, Quique Gonz√°lez, El Drogas, Kutxi Romero, Dani Mart√≠n, Andr√©s Calamaro y Ovidi ‚ÄúZigarros‚Äù. Todos rindiendo homenaje a un compa√±ero, pero tambi√©n a un amigo. Y es ese ‚Äúbuen rollo‚Äù el que al final acaba transmitiendo Fito con su m√∫sica. Canciones que, cronol√≥gicamente y de manera inversa, nos permiten hacer un recorrido por sus √∫ltimos 20 a√±os. Temas que suenan a rock and roll, claro, pero tambi√©n a country, rock urbano, tex-mex o pub-rock. Con su verborrea habitual. Porque lo que hace Fito es f√°cil, pero no es f√°cil hacerlo como Fito. Queriendo a su profesi√≥n y honr√°ndola con la manera de ofrecerse a su p√∫blico una noche s√≠ y otra tambi√©n. Algo que lo ha convertido, por derecho propio, en un grande de la m√∫sica de este pa√≠s. Y una prueba m√°s de ello es este Fitograf√≠a. Porque no iba a conformarse el de Bilbao con un recopilatorio al uso. Para eso no se esperan 20 a√±os. Fito ha querido ir m√°s all√°. Y se ha vuelto a vaciar para su gente. Ofreci√©ndoles su m√∫sica, claro, pero tambi√©n textos e im√°genes con un nivel de detalle rara vez visto en este pa√≠s. Para algunos nos es imposible no sentarnos a escuchar estas canciones y recordar la primera vez que o√≠mos el encanto de ‚ÄúRojitas las orejas‚Äù, la m√°gica palabrer√≠a de ‚ÄúA la luna se le ve el ombligo‚Äù o el acorde√≥n mexicano de ‚ÄúWhisky Barato‚Äù. Todas esas palabras en el lugar perfecto en ‚ÄúPor la boca vive el pez‚Äù o la sutilidad sugerente de ‚ÄúMe equivocar√≠a otra vez‚Äù. Incluso ese ‚ÄúEntre dos mares‚Äù, extra√≠da del repertorio de Platero y T√∫, y regrabada para la ocasi√≥n en un nuevo regalo para sus seguidores para llevarnos a tiempos pret√©ritos encaja a la perfecci√≥n. Trocitos humildes del alma de un m√∫sico. Un Fito que, mientras nosotros disfrutamos de esta excelente box-set ya estar√° planeando sus nuevos pasos. Nuevos horizontes, nuevas autopistas. snippet.description:
Arcangelo Corelli - Christmas Concerto Grosso, Op. 6 No. 8 in G Minor, Fatto per la Notte di Natale - III. Adagio, 1714.

Although one cannot be sure, Arcangelo Corelli's famous Christmas Concerto -- the Concerto grosso in G minor, Op. 6, No. 8 ("Fatto per la notte di Natale," as the inscription actually reads) - may well have been composed a full quarter century before it first appeared in print, posthumously, in 1714; there is a record of Corelli having, in 1690, performed a Christmas Concerto for the enjoyment of his then-new patron, Cardinal Pietro Ottoboni. The Christmas Concerto is easily Corelli's best-known piece of music, though isolated movements from the sonatas have, through other composers' adaptations, achieved vast individual fame. It is at heart an example of the sonata da chiesa, expanded from the usual four movements to five and incorporating into the last movement a rolling, 12/8 meter Pastorale ad libitum. Like the rest of the Op. 6 concerti, it is scored for a concertante group consisting of two violins and a cello and a larger tutti ensemble. 

The normal slow-fast-slow-fast organization of the sonata da chiesa underlies everything that happens in the Christmas Concerto; but Corelli at several key points makes a concerted effort to turn that textbook organization on its head. Six measures of fiery Vivace preface the opening Grave movement, and the third movement (Adagio) has a central Allegro episode in which the first solo violin and first tutti violins suddenly break out with a rapid, ruffled sixteenth note oscillation (complex first movement structures that incorporate many changes of tempo are not at all unusual throughout Op. 6, indeed, the opening movement of Op. 6, No. 1 has no fewer than seven tempo indications in it!). 

BYU-I University Orchestra
7.IX.2010. Clarissa Lunt conducting.

Concerto grosso in G minor, Op. 6, No. 8 (Christmas Concerto)
Fatto per la notte di Natale

snippet.description:
A video recording boys' reaction when asked to hit a girl has been filmed by Counties Manukau Police in their ongoing campaign against family violence.

The clip, which features seven boys aged 8 to 12, has taken a cue from "Slap Her", an Italian clip that gained world-wide attention earlier this year.

It begins with an interviewer asking the boys their names, ages, and what they want to be. They are introduced to a girl called Chloe, asked to make her laugh, and give her a hug.

Asked why they like her, one responds, "there's just something nice about Chloe".

The boys are then asked to slap her.

"I'm not slapping a girl!" the first boy says. The others, looking a mix of perplexed and horrified, also refuse. "That's the wrong thing to do!" "She's a girl." "You can't just go around hitting people," they say.

The video ends with the words: "If kids know it's wrong you should too."

Counties Manukau district prevention officer Senior Constable Gary Boles said they had used the Italian video as inspiration. "It was our first instinct, to see our boys would react. 
He said the students are from Bucklands Beach Primary school, and although parents were shown the Italian clip, the Kiwi boys weren't prepped, other than being asked to think about what they wanted to be when they grew up.

"Everyone was under strict instructions. We wanted the raw feeling and emotion to come out. The result you see is the result we wanted," Mr Boles said.

Chloe was the daughter of a local police officer, he said, and was "perfect" for the role.

The video was shot over two weeks, and released today to remind people of the "It's not OK" message in time for Christmas.

"For us it's a high family violence time of the year. We want to tell everyone, if you're getting heated up, just take five, walk away, get a breath of fresh air," Mr Boles said.

"It's a time for having fun and not for violence."

The video had a reach of 20,000 in its first two hours.

-NZH

Get ready to know JLaw like you‚Äôve never known her before.
When it comes to Jennifer Lawrence, many see her as an open book, because, well, she‚Äôs just so darn open about almost everything in her life. BUT, be that as it may, there‚Äôs definitely a lot of things that we don‚Äôt know about her. Sure, she‚Äôs one of the most relatable celebs out there and as nice as she is, there are just some things she won‚Äôt do out in public. Like take selfies with fans. 
In her Vogue spread, JLaw revealed that she will almost always meet with fans, butttttt she won‚Äôt always say yes to a selfie. She said QUOTE, ‚ÄúI‚Äôm happy to meet people, give autographs, shake hands, and say ‚ÄòThank you.‚Äô I wouldn‚Äôt have a job if people weren‚Äôt going to see my movies. It‚Äôs just‚Ä¶if I‚Äôm on an airplane and I have no makeup on, I don‚Äôt want to take a selfie that‚Äôs going to end up on E!‚Äù Fair enough! Hey, we all have our own selfie preferences, some of us just don‚Äôt like to take makeup free selfies. 
Although Jennifer likes to keep a lot of her private life, private, the actress actually opened up about her boyfriend Darren Aronofsky to the magazine and why she was attracted to him before they started dating. JLaw said, ‚ÄúWe had energy. I had energy for him. I don‚Äôt know how he felt about me. I normally don‚Äôt like Harvard people, because they can‚Äôt go two minutes without mentioning that they went to Harvard. He‚Äôs not like that‚Ä¶For the past year, I‚Äôve been dealing with him as a human. I‚Äôve been in relationships before where I am just confused. And I‚Äôm never confused with him.‚Äù

Good news is, Jen revealed that the two are currently meeting with directors for the film AND she revealed a bit of the storyline, saying that it‚Äôs about QUOTE, ‚Äòdysfunctional twins. snippet.description:
It‚Äôs certainly easier to make assumptions about people than it is to spend time getting to know someone. We wanted to put assumptions to the test to see what we're missing out on because we're so busy assuming we already "know" a person. Join us as we discover why you should never judge a book by it‚Äôs cover in our series 'Tell My Story, Blind Date.'

We are all conditioned with certain biases. In this experiment, we challenged these biases by asking people to guess their partner's interests and past experiences based only on their partner's appearance. When they learned their partner's real answers, they were shocked by how wrong they were.

Now tell YOUR story. What do people assume about you?

Jennifer Lawrence explains she is ‚Äúreally rude‚Äù to fans and why she definitely WON‚ÄôT take a selfie with you!
J.Law is unapologetic about her new personality trait: rudeness.
‚ÄòPassengers‚Äô star Jennifer Lawrence is known for her constant truth bombs. Weeks after Jennifer revealed she‚Äôs QUOTE ‚Äúscared of her fans‚Äù, the actress has now proclaimed she is also really rude to them. In a candid phone interview with the Daily Telegraph Jen explains her recent mood change saying QUOTE, ‚ÄúI have just started becoming really rude and drawn into myself because I have to protect my bubble that is just like, ‚ÄòI have a weird job -- don‚Äôt let this be a reality.‚Äô‚Äù Adding that maintaining her sense of self is more important to her than someone thinking she is rude. So what kind of rudeness can we expect if we‚Äôre lucky enough to bump into Jen while out and about? Jennifer detailed QUOTE, ‚ÄúSo I make it clear by my body language that I don‚Äôt want to be talking to a stranger. And if they keep talking to me, I just get rude. I don‚Äôt say anything but I am just like, ‚Äòmmm-hmmm, yep, nope, OK, bye‚Äô.‚Äù
So try not to take it personally when Jennifer Lawrence coldly walks away from you on the street. And if you thought about asking Jen for a selfie- think again! The actress also told the Daily Telegraph QUOTE, ‚ÄúI need it -- otherwise I just wouldn‚Äôt go out. Because I would be like, ‚ÄòYeah, I love you too - oh my God, we‚Äôre such good friends, let‚Äôs take a selfie‚Äô. I would be doing that with 50 people a day. You can‚Äôt live like that.‚Äù
I have to be honest, I sincerely do understand where Jen is coming from. Jenifer Lawerence and Katy Perry JUST met on the Golden Globes red carpet and saying it was AMAZING is a bit of an under statement.

And by something special, I‚Äôm talking about this moment between our favorite pop star and Hollywood‚Äôs leading young lady. Jenifer Lawrence crossed paths with Katy Perry when Jen stopped by Katy‚Äôs interview with Ryan Seacrest on E!  Ryan was casually talking about Katy‚Äôs recent tweet that praised Jenifer Lawerence and David O Russell‚Äôs work in their recent film ‚ÄòJoy‚Äô because Katy tweeted ‚ÄúJust saw "JOY". Like an 'as seen on TV' Bump-it‚Ä¶" Keep in mind at this point in time JLAW is literally petting Katy‚Äôs hair as she continued‚Ä¶  "It's like a loaf of bread for later." 

They didn‚Äôt stop at hair though, Katy then told the Golden Globe-nominated actress about her experience seeing Joy by saying

"I was like, ‚ÄòI can make it in the world! You inspired me!" but Lawrence seemingly knows who Katy is (because who doesn‚Äôt) and said

Sooo basically it‚Äôs everything we‚Äôve ever dreamed of and possibly a little bit more‚Ä¶  Two girls meet, they praise each other AND a ton of touching and hugging was involved‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm NOW just waiting for some sort of collaboration between the two.

Lawrence made some crazy faces and even divulged that she thought about pushing Taylor down the stairs‚Äîand it looks like Ryan isn't done talking about the moment quite yet! 

The E! host brought up the incident at the 2014 Grammy Awards and being the good sport Taylor is, she told Ryan she thought the photobomb was "amazing." 

But that's not all, Taylor even went as far to send Taylor a personal message that Ryan will deliver to Jennifer at the Academy Awards that are coming up in March. 

Saying, "Thanks for your friendship and thank for making amazing, terrifying faces behind me on camera when I'm trying to do an interview and not mess up. Good luck. I hope you win. I hope you win everything all the time." 

Funny thing, Lawrence actually admitted she didn't know Taylor was actually on camera -- or at least didn't think the interview was live! 

Well, it definitely was and we're SO glad the moment was caught on tape‚Äîbut really let's talk about this Best Friend kind of support from Taylor to Jennifer. 

Jennifer already snagged an award at the Golden Globes for best supporting actress and the whole cast of American Hustle took it home at the SAG awards, but now we'll just have to wait and see if Lawrence will win yet again for Best Supporting Actress at the Oscars. 

And if it's up to Taylor, she'll win everything all the time! More Celebrity News ‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ http://bit.ly/SubClevverNews

So let me get this straight ‚Äì Kim fangirled over Jen who was fangirling over Kim, and now I‚Äôm fangirling over the fact that these two are fangirling over each other. I think I need to sit down for a sec.

Jennifer Lawrence has made it crystal clear in the past that she is the Kardashian‚Äôs #1 fan, and don‚Äôt you dare even think to @ her on that. But more recently, she upped her undying obsession for the famous family when she revealed that the entire Kardashian clan was responsible for keeping her sane while filming her upcoming thriller ‚ÄúMother.‚Äù

Jen got candid about how dark and psychologically twisted ‚ÄúMother‚Äù became, as it started messing with her emotions and putting her in dark place mentally, to which her boyfriend and the film‚Äôs director, Darren Aronofsky, created a Kardashian tent for her to escape to, filled with the family‚Äôs photos and Kardashian reruns playing on a loop during all hours of the day.

But the tables have officially turned, and the QUEEN of E!, Kim Kardashian herself, was at home minding her own business, when she flipped on the TV network to find the exact moment Jennifer began gushing over how vital the family was to her well-being.

Kim then took to Snapchat to share the part of Jen‚Äôs E! interview talking about the Kardashians, writing alongside it, ‚ÄúOMG is this real?!‚Äù Well I‚Äôve got news for you Kimmy ‚Äì start believing it. Jen has been so open about her admiration for reality TV, specifically the Kardashians, that she‚Äôd even choose them over the Real Housewives. She said QUOTE, ‚ÄúThe Kardashians are more comforting to me, I think. I've been watching them for 11 years, so I grew up with them, and I know all of them personally. The Housewives, they go in and out. They're fighting all the time. There's something more comforting about the Kardashians.‚Äù

And although Jen has yet to meet Kim or any of her sisters, she DID receive a surprise birthday treat from the head honcho of the fam, Kris Jenner, who delivered a cake to her surprise birthday back in 2015. Jen recalled QUOTE, ‚ÄúIt was the closest I‚Äôve ever come to losing consciousness. I had no idea. I‚Äôd never met her before, but we‚Äôve always watched Keeping Up With the Kardashians. And then Kris Jenner and I sang ‚ÄòBuild Me Up Buttercup‚Äô on karaoke.‚Äù

I can only imagine the level of pure fangirl that would go down if Jen were to ever meet Kim, so while we wait for that day to come, I want to know what you guys thought about this whole series of events that went down between Jen and Kim, so hit us up in the comments, and after that, click right over here to see if Kylie and Jordyn legitimately tied the knot. Thanks for hanging out with me here on Clevver News, I‚Äôm Joslyn Davis and I‚Äôll see you next time.
